longBusinessSummary: Ellaktor S.A., through its subsidiaries, engages in the construction and quarrying, real estate development and management, wind power, environment, and concession businesses. The company constructs bridges, motorways, metro projects, biological treatment plants, natural gas pipelines, refineries, shopping centers, casinos, tourist and hotel units, cultural centers, hospitals, airports, Olympic and athletic complexes, railway projects, tunnels, dams, port projects, energy production stations, electromechanical projects, etc.; and logistics, office, residential, industrial, and educational buildings. It is also involved in the waste management and energy production, which include design, construction, and operation of waste treatment plant, as well as offers alternative fuel production and biomass exploitation projects. In addition, the company develops, constructs, and operates wind farms; provides real estate development and services, which consists of retail parks, entertainment centers, residential complexes, exhibition centers, and offices and mixed use buildings; and provides consultancy and services to third parties. Ellaktor S.A. operates in Greece, other European countries, Gulf countries, the Americas, Africa, and Australia. The company was formerly known as ELLINIKI TECHNODOMIKI TEB SA and changed its name to Ellaktor S.A. in 2008. Ellaktor S.A. is based in Athens, Greece.  As per the transaction announced on January 8, 2021, Ellaktor S.A. operates as a subsidiary of Reggeborgh Invest B.V.
